title: Transformations
description:
Manos Hadjidakis was one of the most popular Greek composers. Although coming from a small country, he won worldwide acclaim in the &#039;60s for the music he wrote for films like "Never on Sunday" and "Stella". 
Here, as a tribute, K.B. transforms some of Hadjidakis&#039;s tunes into electronic and drum &#039;n&#039; bass chill-out sounds.

It&#039;s sweet, melodic, maybe a bit ethnic. Worth the try if you&#039;re looking for something different.
